        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): add agentId selector to usage page for multi-agent session scoping",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd `usageAgentId` state and an agent selector dropdown to the Control UI usage page so operators can explicitly scope `sessions.usage` requests to a specific agent. When no agent is selected, the backend's existing scoped default applies.\n\nThe v2026.5.17 fix (6a12c6f79915 / #81386) properly scoped `sessions.usage` lookups by `agentId`. The Web UI was never updated to send `agentId`, so non-main agent sessions were invisible on the usage page. This PR adds the missing frontend support without changing the backend security boundary.\n\nAgent dropdown options are populated from the configured agents list (`agents.list` API), with a fallback to session-derived agent IDs when the list is unavailable. The currently selected agent is always preserved in the dropdown.\n\nThis revision also:\n- updates the shared app view-state type and generated Control UI i18n outputs\n- adds an explicit older-gateway compatibility gate for selected `agentId` requests instead of silently falling back to default-agent data\n- aligns the default selector label and filtered daily chart behavior with the backend's real default-agent semantics\n- adds mocked multi-agent Control UI browser proof with redacted local artifacts\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\nThe Web UI usage page `loadUsage` never sent `agentId` in `sessions.usage` requests. The backend correctly defaults omitted `agentId` to the configured default agent. This PR adds a client-side agent selector dropdown populated from configured agents so operators can choose which agent's usage to query.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** The Control UI usage page had no way to request non-default-agent sessions from `sessions.usage`. The dropdown also mislabeled the empty state as all agents, and selected-agent requests had no explicit behavior for older gateways that reject the newer `agentId` param.\n\n**Real environment tested:** macOS 26, Node 24, branch `fix/usage-agent-filter-87132`, commit `8befcc6bd788d30917877182fed774e65c5ef318`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```bash\nnode --import tsx scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts check\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/usage.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/usage-agent-selector.e2e.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n- `control-ui-i18n` check passes clean after regenerating locale outputs.\n- Focused regression tests pass:\n  - `ui/src/ui/controllers/usage.node.test.ts` covers sending `agentId`, omitting it when unset, and surfacing a remembered compatibility error when an older gateway rejects `agentId`.\n  - `ui/src/ui/views/usage.test.ts` covers the configured-agent selector and the corrected `Default agent` empty option.\n- Mocked multi-agent Control UI browser proof passes end to end:\n  - The `/usage` page renders the configured agent selector with `Default agent`, `main`, and `opus`.\n  - Selecting `opus` loads the `Opus session` row in the rendered UI.\n  - The browser-side mocked gateway captures a real `sessions.usage` request with `agentId: \"opus\"`.\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n- The usage selector is populated from configured agents, not only from already-returned sessions.\n- The empty selector state now accurately means the backend's default-agent scope.\n- Selecting a non-default agent sends `agentId` in the `sessions.usage` payload.\n- If an older gateway rejects the `agentId` field, the UI now shows a precise unsupported-gateway error instead of silently showing default-agent data.\n- Agent-filtered daily charts now stay aligned with the selected session set rather than reusing cross-agent daily totals.\n\n**Artifacts (private/local, redacted):**\n- `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/usage-agent-selector/usage-default-agent.png`\n- `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/usage-agent-selector/usage-opus-agent.png`\n- `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/usage-agent-selector/page@396db59f56116564a3b5e01125757c6e.webm`\n\n**What was not tested:** A live multi-agent gateway with real persisted session stores was not exercised in this PR proof run; the browser proof uses the repo's mocked Control UI gateway harness to verify request wiring and visible UI behavior deterministically.\n\nFixes #87132\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/usage-agent-filter-87132",
